# Memory bank workflow (required)

**Before** you plan or implement any user-requested change:

1. Read [.cursor/memory-bank/projectbrief.md](.cursor/memory-bank/projectbrief.md) for goals, stack, and pointers.
2. Read [.cursor/memory-bank/CHANGELOG.md](.cursor/memory-bank/CHANGELOG.md) for the latest shipped decisions and edits.
3. Open [.cursor/memory-bank/PRD.md](.cursor/memory-bank/PRD.md) when the work touches routes, copy, CTAs, SEO, data shapes, or design tokens defined there.

**After** you finish a substantive change (new feature, bugfix, refactor, dependency, or content update):

1. Append a dated section to `CHANGELOG.md` (newest at top): what changed, which areas/files, and any follow-ups.
2. If scope or stack shifted, update `projectbrief.md` in the same folder (keep it short).

Do not skip updates when the user only asked for a “small” change — still log one line in `CHANGELOG.md` so the next session stays aligned.
